{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"text":"? = nil) ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This method is intended for language bindings. If writing in C,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_initable_new()"},{"type":"text","text":" should typically be used instead."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The object must be initialized before any real use after initial","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"construction, either with this function or "},{"code":"g_async_initable_init_async()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementations may also support cancellation. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"then initialization can be cancelled by triggering the cancellable object"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"from another thread. If the operation was cancelled, the error","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancelled"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned. If "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"cancellable"},{"text":" is not ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the object doesn’t support cancellable initialization the error"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"notSupported"},{"text":" will be returned.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If the object is not initialized, or initialization returns with an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"error, then all operations on the object except ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_object_ref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_unref()"},{"type":"text","text":" are considered to be invalid, and have undefined"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"behaviour. See the ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","isActive":true},{"text":" for more details.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Callers should not assume that a class which implements "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" can be","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"initialized multiple times, unless the class explicitly documents itself as"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"supporting this. Generally, a class’ implementation of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"init()"},{"text":" can assume","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(and assert) that it will only be called once. Previously, this documentation"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"recommended all ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable"},{"type":"text","text":" implementations should be idempotent; that"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"recommendation was relaxed in GLib 2.54."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If a class explicitly supports being initialized multiple times, it is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"recommended that the method is idempotent: multiple calls with the same"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"arguments should return the same results. Only the first call initializes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the object; further calls return the result of the first call."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"One reason why a class might need to support idempotent initialization is if","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"it is designed to be used via the singleton pattern, with a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"GObjectClass.constructor","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that sometimes returns an existing instance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"In this pattern, a caller would expect to be able to call "},{"code":"g_initable_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on the result of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_object_new()"},{"type":"text","text":", regardless of whether it is in fact a new"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instance.","type":"text"}]}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface."}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"GIO","role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"externalID":"s:3GIO16InitableProtocolPAAE5init_11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO22PowerProfileMonitorRefV","symbolKind":"method","title":"init_(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"init_"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/powerprofilemonitorref\/init_(cancellable:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init_(cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/AsyncInitable":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","title":"AsyncInitable","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/asyncinitable","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AsyncInitable","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"code":"GAsyncInitable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is an interface for asynchronously initializable objects."}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/Initable":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/initable","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"Initable","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Initable","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/Initable","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInitable"},{"type":"text","text":" is implemented by objects that can fail during"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"initialization. If an object implements this interface then","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"it must be initialized as the first thing after construction,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"either via [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.Initable.init"},{"text":"] or [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Gio.AsyncInitable.init_async"},{"type":"text","text":"]"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(the latter is only available if it also implements [iface","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/AsyncInitable","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"])."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Initable"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/PowerProfileMonitorRef/init_(cancellable:)":{"role":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Initializes the object implementing the interface."}],"kind":"symbol","title":"init_(cancellable:)","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/powerprofilemonitorref\/init_(cancellable:)","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"init_","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"CancellableRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/init_(cancellable:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/PowerProfileMonitorRef/InitableProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"InitableProtocol Implementations","kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","abstract":[],"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/powerprofilemonitorref\/initableprotocol-implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef\/InitableProtocol-Implementations","type":"topic"},"#iface@Gio.Initable#description":{"title":"description","url":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description","type":"link","titleInlineContent":[{"text":"description","type":"text"}],"identifier":"#iface@Gio.Initable#description"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/PowerProfileMonitorRef":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/PowerProfileMonitorRef","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PowerProfileMonitorRef"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"PowerProfileMonitorRef","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"PowerProfileMonitorRef","role":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/powerprofilemonitorref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GPowerProfileMonitor"},{"type":"text","text":" makes it possible for applications as well as OS"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"components to monitor system power profiles and act upon them. It currently"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"only exports whether the system is in “Power Saver” mode (known as","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"“Low Power” mode on some systems).","type":"text"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"}}}